						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Mantrapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 23+1:</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription may be assigned on palaeographical grounds to c. 13th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 500 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> for maintaining a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp by a certain Ammaiyāḻvān Vīdiviṭaṅkap-perumāḷ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Urāyarāman, a native of Puduppaṭṭaṇam. He is one among the persons who is referred to as <hi rend="italic">Umbarśānattār.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
